e at ppb-ppm levels, and the report treats meteorites as an unambiguous natural source of prebiotic leucine. This step is partly representational rather than a single in situ Earth-surface reaction, but is included to connect exogenous delivery into the same network and is explicitly grounded in meteoritic evidence."}], "pathways": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "name": "Classical Strecker route from branched aldehyde", "description": "Hydrothermal small-carbonyl production feeds surface branched aldehyde formation, followed by canonical Strecker synthesis and aminonitrile hydrolysis to leucine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005", "mol_006", "mol_008", "mol_010"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "name": "H2S volcanic spark-assisted Strecker route", "description": "Sulfur-rich spark discharge supplies HCN while hydrothermal aldehydes are branched at the surface, then Strecker chemistry yields leucine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_005", "rxn_002", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_004", "mol_008", "mol_010"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "name": "Hydrothermal protometabolic keto-acid route", "description": "CO2 reduction leads to pyruvate, chain extension forms alpha-ketoisocaproate, and Ni-catalyzed reductive amination yields leucine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_003", "rxn_010", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_013", "mol_012", "mol_009"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "Aldehyde-fed keto-acid route to reductive amination", "description": "Hydrothermal acetaldehyde supports alpha-ketoisocaproate chain extension from pyruvate, followed by direct reductive amination to leucine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_010", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_006", "mol_012", "mol_009"]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "name": "Alanine-mediated transamination route", "description": "Pyruvate first becomes alanine under hydrothermal alkaline conditions, while parallel keto-acid chain 