hway_coherence\": 0.76,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.87,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.9,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.75,\n      \"feedback\": \"This integrated HCN-fed Bucherer-Bergs route is conceptually coherent and uses literature-supported HCN generation. Its weakness is cumulative: multiple speculative upstream steps are stacked before a moderately plausible hydantoin route. The pathway is not implausible, but confidence is limited by the chain-assembly gap.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_003\",\n        \"rxn_010\",\n        \"rxn_012\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Improve the alpha-ketoisocaproate synthesis sequence before invoking Bucherer-Bergs conversion.\",\n        \"Distinguish between spark-generated HCN supply and pool-phase hydantoin formation conditions.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.72,\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.95,\n        \"rxn_006\": 0.48,\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.91,\n        \"rxn_008\": 0.88\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.8,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.87,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.94,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.9,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.85,\n      \"feedback\": \"This is the best integrated environmental narrative in the network: hydrothermal reduced-carbon generation, transfer to sulfur-rich surface spark/discharge chemistry, then aqueous Strecker and hydrolysis. The route aligns well with the literature emphasis that no single setting optimally supports the full pathway. The principal remaining issue is still the underdeveloped chemistry of branched aldehyde formation.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_006\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Provide a more explicit environmental handoff from hydrothermal products to surface pools.\",\n       