 \"pathway_coherence\": 0.7,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.82,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.94,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.73,\n      \"feedback\": \"This route benefits from two literature-supported nodes: pyruvate-to-alanine by iron oxyhydroxides and alpha-ketoisocaproate-to-leucine by Ni/H2 reductive amination. But the actual bridge to alpha-ketoisocaproate remains underjustified. As drawn, it mixes solid literature-supported termini with a speculative core branch-construction step.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_015\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Provide a documented route from small aldehydes/keto acids to alpha-ketoisocaproate rather than a single lumped construction step.\",\n        \"State whether rxn_004 is being used as an analogy or as an actual pathway feeder, since alanine is not directly required in this route.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.82,\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.58,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.93,\n        \"rxn_015\": 0.34,\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.79\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.66,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.74,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.86,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.88,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.72,\n      \"feedback\": \"The transamination logic is reasonable and does align broadly with Varma, Muchowska, and Moran-type chemistry, and alanine generation from pyruvate is well supported by Barge et al. The problem again is that alpha-ketoisocaproate is not generated by a well-supported preceding step. Thus the pathway is chemically intelligible but not yet robust as a fully prebiotic route.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_003\",\n        \"rxn_015\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Strengthen the provenance of alpha-ketoisocaproate.\",\n        \"Include explicit catalys